question: How did Harry propose?
answer:
Oh I had so much fun writing this! Thank you for requesting! 

__________________________

I imagine him being very nervous.

Maybe he took you for a walk while you were visiting Anne. He had been acting a bit differently for a while now but you could clearly see his nervousness peaking when you were on your way to spend the week at Anne’s house.

You had asked him about it but he had always just shrugged your comments off. Saying that he was fine and nothing was going on.

You were worried but weren’t going to push Harry into talking about it. You knew how much he hated that. He would tell you eventually.

So when he asked you on Wednesday morning if you would take a walk with him after breakfast, you knew he was ready to tell you what was bothering him.

During the walk you could feel his hand shaking in yours. ‘Harry, are you okay? I know you don’t like me pressuring into saying things but you’re shaking.’ You said and stood in front of him, your hands holding his arms.

‘I am fine. I am just nervous.’ He said and didn’t look you in the eyes. Your heart fell because you could clearly see he was troubled and whenever Harry feels miserable so do you.

‘Please talk to me.’ You said trying to find his eyes.

Harry took a deep breath and looked you in the eyes taking your hands in his.

‘YN.’ He said and took a pause.

‘I love you so much, like I can’t even describe how much I love you. You are the most amazing thing that could ever happen to me. We have known each other for 4 years now and I have never been so happy than I have been with you. So now I would like to ask you to take the next step into our relationship together.’

Harry went down and sat on one knee and pulled out the ring.

‘YN, will you marry me?’ He asked and all you could do was nod. You had a lump in your throat and tears were falling down your cheeks.

‘Yes Harry I will.’ and after you said that you could see tears swelling in Harry’s eyes as well. He slipped the ring around your finger and kissed you.

You couldn’t help but laugh in the kiss, you were just so happy.
